    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what I found and the plan I've put together:\n\n---\n\n### What `uv cache stats` needs to do\n\nShow a per-bucket breakdown of cache disk usage (11 buckets: wheels, sdists, flat-index, git, interpreter, simple, archive, builds, environments, python, binaries) followed by a grand total. Supports `--human` / `-H` for human-readable sizes. Gated behind `--preview` like `cache size`.\n\n---\n\n### Plan overview (8 steps, 6 files modified, 2 files created)\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheBucket::name()` method returning short labels (`\"wheels\"`, `\"sdists\"`, etc.). Important: `CacheBucket::iter()` intentionally omits `Python`; the stats command will use its own inline array that includes all 11 buckets.\n\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to the `CacheCommand` enum, plus a `StatsArgs` struct with the same `--human`/`-H`/`--human-readable` flag as `SizeArgs`.\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — The handler: iterates all 11 buckets, calls `diskus::DiskUsage` per-bucket path, accumulates a total, then prints a fixed-width table. Uses existing `human_readable_bytes()` utility.\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Declare `mod cache_stats` and re-export `cache_stats`.\n\n5. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add the dispatch match arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)`.\n\n6. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` (next available bit after `ProjectDirectoryMustExist = 1 << 27`), wire it into `as_str()`, `from_str`, and the test assertions.\n\n7. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` helper on `TestContext`.\n\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Three integration tests (empty-raw, with-packages-raw, with-packages-human), auto-discovered by Cargo.",
